data.value: There are some bowlers who are known more for their never-say-die spirit rather than their skill set. Peter Siddle would fall into that category - a tireless workhorse who was a captain's dream. The Victorian was blessed with a nice flowing bowling action and had the ability to generate disconcerting bounce off the track. His unerring accuracy was what made him a threat to the batsman because Siddle barely gave anything away.
